The paper focuses on analyzing the quality of web APIs, which are a type of software component. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the impact of geo-distribution on API quality, which relates to distributed computing (cs.DC). The assessment of API security measurements falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the impact of API quality on user experience, which relates to networked systems (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for creating tools and approaches to mitigate quality issues, which falls under programming languages (cs.PL).
